Name: Your Star Wars RPG game master, let me be.
Project description: With over 100 hours of experience guiding groups through the immersive world of Fantasy Flight's Star Wars RPG, I'm ready to lead your team on thrilling adventures across the Star Wars galaxy. Utilizing the dynamic SWRPG system, you'll have the opportunity to bring your wildest Star Wars dreams to life and shape the fate of your characters. Leveraging advanced AI and technology, remote SWRPG sessions are now more accessible than ever. Using platforms like Roll20 and Discord, we can easily schedule flexible playtimes that suit your group's needs.
Project details: iGotchu is an app that just...gets you, so, we designed with a diverse array of hand models.

Name: Favorite Technologies
Project description: Ruby, Rails, JavaScript, PostgreSQL, Node.js, Selenium, React, Unreal Engine, AWS, Docker, Kubernetes, and whatever else I can get my hands on!
Project details: Sinder is a dating app for single socks. The design concept stems from the mission of the company: to help single socks meet their match. Simple, elegant, and cheerful tones convey the optimism of this company's mission.

Name: About Myself
Project description: I am a devoted son, husband and father, an adventurer exploring the galaxies, an engineer and rocket-man, a Jedi seeking knowledge as both a student and a teacher, and a steadfast friend always ready to extend a helping hand. I find great joy in aiding others and acquiring knowledge and embrace every opportunity to witness the vast wonders life offers. Thriving on grand adventures and cherished camaraderie, my life's purpose centers on relentless exploration and boundless learning. With an unwavering passion, my aim is not just for the stars but to delve beyond, fueled by unyielding determination. I am a Jedi, an instrument of peace; Where there is hatred, I shall bring love; Where there is injury, pardon; Where there is doubt, faith; Where there is despair, hope; Where there is darkness, light; And where there is sadness, joy. I am a Jedi.
Image description: Friends on top of the world
Project details:
This project has made it to the sun, hence the blank yellow sun-like screen. It's confirmed that, contrary to popular belief, there is no life on the sun. My design concept for this mission conveys simultaneous emptiness and optimism for finding life beyond earth, and the sun, apparently.
